results.name: Number of 3 X 3 matrices whose determinant is 1 mod n.
comment: Order of the group SL(3,Z_n). For n > 2, a(n) is divisible by 48. - _Jianing Song_, Nov 24 2018
link: T. D. Noe, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
Geoffrey Critzer, Combinatorics of Vector Spaces over Finite Fields, Master's thesis, Emporia State University, 2018.
formula: Multiplicative with a(p^e) = p^(8*e-5)*(p^3 - 1)*(p^2 - 1). - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Nov 18 2001
mathematica: a[n_] := (n^9*Times @@ Function[p, (1 - 1/p^3)*(1 - 1/p^2)*(1 - 1/p)] /@ FactorInteger[n][[All, 1]])/EulerPhi[n]; a[1] = 1; Array[a, 30] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Mar 21 2017 *)
program: (PARI) a(n) = n^9*prod(k=2, n, if (!isprime(k) || (n % k), 1, (1-1/k^3)*(1-1/k^2)*(1-1/k)))/eulerphi(n); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jun 30 2015
